						<summary>

						<p>This is in Sanskrit and not dated. It refers itself to the reign of <hi rend="bold">Harihara.</hi> It states that he made gifts according to <hi rend="italic">Hēmādri-śāstra</hi> and records that he made a grant of the village <hi rend="bold">Chimmanakeṟe,</hi> situated in <hi rend="bold">Gutti-vaḷita</hi> in <hi rend="bold">Ghanādri-rājya</hi> to the learned Brāhman <hi rend="bold">Gōpalārādhya,</hi> son of <hi rend="bold">Viṭhalārādhya.</hi> The king referred to here was probably Harihara II.</p>						

						</summary>
